  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age at diagnosis ≥ 18 to ≤ 55 years

          -  Employed at the time of entry into the care pathway

          -  Presenting a head and neck cancer (excluding nasal), stage I, II and III, under a
             first anti-tumor treatment (surgery, radiotherapy, or chemotherapy)

          -  Patient mastering the French language

          -  Affiliated with social security

          -  Consent signed by the patient before the implementation of any specific procedure to
             studyAnnuler les modificationsAlpha

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Having been treated for another cancer before (except skin cancer and / or prostate)

          -  Metastatic disease immediately

          -  Patients unable to undergo regular monitoring

          -  Presenting psychiatric
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
